parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of brake lines can cause the loss of brake fluid, leading to a failure of the braking system, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or there is a sudden loss of braking power. In some cases
the brake warning light may illuminate
and there may be a hissing or popping noise when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate or no readings on the speedometer, fuel gauge, and other essential gauges, leading to safety issues and potential accidents.
The failure of the throttle control sensor can cause the vehicle to go into reduced power mode, leading to loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle goes into reduced power mode
error codes indicating throttle control sensor failure
and loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, loss of power, and other safety issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Liftgate and Window Lock Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear liftgate and window lock can cause safety issues, particularly when occupants are unable to exit the vehicle in an emergency.
symptoms: Rear liftgate and window will not unlock
inability to exit the vehicle in an emergency.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of interior lighting and accessories can cause safety issues, particularly at night or in low-light conditions.
The failure of the steering column can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clunking or rattling noise in the steering column
jerking or pulling to one side
and vibration in the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and loud noises or vibrations in the power steering system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause the vehicle to lose control, making it difficult or impossible to steer, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clunking or rattling noise in the steering column
and vibration in the steering wheel.
